## The Core Strategy

### Content Mix — Authority-First Framework

LinkedIn in 2026 rewards expert content over personal storytelling. The right split for designers:

- **70% Industry & Expertise** — opinions, case studies, process breakdowns, UX takes, trend analysis, how-tos. This is what builds the reputation that makes the right people reach out.
- **15% Personal / Behind-the-scenes** — career moments, building in public, honest reflections, the messy middle of a project. Humanizes without dominating.
- **15% Conversion** — clear asks: "I'm open to work," portfolio showcase, specific service offers, direct CTA posts. This closes the loop.

### Post Types: Visibility vs Authority

| Type | Goal | When to use |
|------|------|-------------|
| **Authority** | Build credibility with target audience | 2 out of every 3 posts |
| **Visibility** | Reach new people, grow following | 1 out of every 3 posts |
| **Conversion** | Direct ask — job lead, client inquiry | Max 1× per 2 weeks |

The goal is *quality of audience* — the right people seeing the right content — not vanity metrics.

