## LinkedIn Formatting Rules

- **One idea per line.** Hard return after every sentence or thought.
- **No paragraphs longer than 3 lines** before a line break.
- **Hook works on mobile** — test that the first 2 lines are compelling as a standalone preview.
- **Emojis and symbols** (→ • ✓) are fine as anchors — 1–3 per post, not more.
- **Hashtags at the end only** — 2–3 max. More looks spammy.
- **No bullet point lists** inside the post body — write in short punchy sentences instead.

**Good hook examples:**
```
I redesigned a checkout flow in 3 days.
Conversion jumped 38%.
I only changed one thing.
```
```
Most design systems fail in year one.
The tools are fine.
Nobody thought about how the team would actually use it.
```

